text: Who's ready for Amonkhet gods?!
This guy!
They made a Sobek based God. I'm 100% sold. Bets on colors? I'm hoping for tri-colored gods
Shards, please!

Saaame.
Jund Gator
Esper Ibis
Bant Snake
Grixis Anubis
Naya Cat are my guesses
Grixis gator
Gotta be blue
Wouldn't a Gator be Sultai?
Gator's are patient, silent and hide to stalk their prey...that speaks green/blue/black to me.
nothing red about a gator
I wouldn't be opposed to Sultai, but that's a wedge, not a shard.
What's the difference?
they're both 3 color
One is a color and its allies, the other is a color and its enemies.
3 next to each other (allied colors) = shard
Ya dig?
2 opposite of 1 = wedge
Most gators in Magic history are green or black, and assuming shards, Jund would be the only one that fit. That's my reasoning.
angry gator
Ok...now I will as the nube question - why do we care wedge vs. shard?
They're gonna be mono colored. They're in WUBRG order
shut it you
Did you just assume my wedge?
henry, wedges / enemy colors are more rare in genreal
Also, for red argument, Gator god is Sobek who is the god of power, military prowess and fertility
Why does their rarity matter, in terms of this discussion?
I'm not being combative, just curious
it doesnt, up above people speculated its shard-based cycle
Ah...and I suppose WotC have to be consistent within a release?
wizards will usually either do wedge-cycles (khans of tarkir) or shard-cycles (shards of alara)
Also, knowing if it's wedges or shards gives us some speculative information about the kinds of cards we can expect to see.
and commander products have had one year of wedges, one year of sharads

For myself personally, I'm guessing it's shards because Khans of Tarkir was wedge and relatively recent. I'm expecting alternation. I'm also speculating tri-color because we don't have three color gods and I want them

And multicolor are typically more narrow than multi color, and we just got a ton of mono-colored legends in Kaladesh, so I'd hope we see multi.
I speculate a lot though, so feel free to disregard my ramblings, lol
Additionally, we may be seeing -1/-1 counters return!
Very exciting
Nicol bolas himself is also grixis aligned

I just don't think wotc's trying to be sneaky about it. They look like indestructible artifact creatures. They probably won't use devotion again. And the art they released looks like they're in color order. White cat, blue bird, black gator, red hound, green snake.
I really hope they don't use devotion again, it's a cool mechanic but I don't just want more theros gods
Black gator would be black and its allies, so, Grixis.
Devotion was a distinctive keyword they wont so it again
They'll probably use different metrics to make them creatures. Number of cards in hand, for example. Or creatures on the field
Also, I'm really hoping for devotion
I mean, the set has pagan religious themes. Devotion would fit
But three colors would make it sketchy
New Lili from the intro pack costs 5BB. Her +2 puts a -1/-1 counter on a creature!
I would like making them creatures to be an activated ability where you are forced to sacrifice permanents/life/energy/etc. to make them a creature for the turn.
Or to evoke them
New intro Gideon costs 4W also has a +2
Gods shouldn't be allowed to stick around...or make them Legendary Enchantment Aura's - they need an avatar to stay on our plane of existence.
Could be interesting if there was a personal cost to the avatar, such as it gets -1/-1 at each upkeep, or you loose life equal to it's CMC each end step...
Gods should be very powerful, but very circumscribed.
I like the gods as they already exist.
I'll be disappointed if Therosian gods aren't echoed in amonkhey
Given that Egyptian gods had multiple identities, there could be double-face god cards.
I find that unlikely. They just did double faced cards in Innistrad. It would be very cool, though.
They gonna bring back chroma, and then it will be a storm format, with phyrexian oil! Yeah!
Honesty though, I would be really surprised if the gods looked or functioned similarly as the theros gods
I'm not convinced that WotC thinks that the way the gods were sometimes creatures and sometimes not was particularly successful or fun to play with
Ask MaRo on his Tumblr.
that means figuring out how to use Tumblr, and I'm not sure I'm young enough to do that
